The US changes the rules for obtaining a visa
The persons must present themselves to the consulate before the visa application service is discussed; the cost of waiting is reduced accordingly.
As of 10 January 2011, the procedures for applying for a visa in the United States Embassy and in the consulates will change.
In the new procedure, most applicants must present themselves to the visa application services (ASC, the initial letters in English) prior to their consultation in the consulate.
The staff of the ASC shall record the biometric data of the applicant, which shall be reviewed by the consulate before the interview.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total cost of handling the visa is reduced, as it is no longer necessary to pay separately the deadline, the processing of the visa request and the transport service with which the document is handed out.
The applicant shall make only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the counterparty to 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including visas for time workers) and 390 dollars for hands and investors.
Those who only want to extend their visa do not have to talk to the consulate, they only have to imagine themselves at the nearest ASC, where they are presenting their documents and their fingerprints are taken.
As the biometric data is collected in the ASC, applicants who need a second date for consultation in the Consulate remain there less time than before.
Those applying for the visa in the consulates of Ciudad Chihuahua, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo no longer have to pay the service charge of $26.
For additional information on the new visa application procedure, please visit the following website: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
