Furthermore, the hack steak, tuna from the bushes, even the baguette and gum of pesticides and other chemicals were spun.
The analyses have brought the presence of nitrates and chloroform to light in the conduction water.
At dinner, the salmon steak with 34 determined chemical residues was the “most abundant” and even the plastic plate used to warm up the meal in the microwave was not without charge.
According to the study, the final risk of this 'damage cocktail' for consumers is likely to be underestimated.
The ‘Alliance Europe Ecology-Les Verts’ (EE-LV) has proposed, on the other hand, ‘in view of the urgency of the situation’, to introduce a moratorium on the use of pesticides to stop the ‘increase in civilisation diseases’.
In July a study by the European Food Safety Authority (EFSA) identified 365 different pesticides identified in fruit and vegetables consumed in Europe, including 76 in cereals.
